At 2:52:42 if you can't instantiate migration class...this should work in PHP 8.1:

className = pathinfo($migration, PATHINFO_FILENAME);
$class = "app\migrations\\" . $className;
$instance = new $class;
 echo "Applying migration $migration ..." . PHP_EOL;
 $instance->up();
 echo "Applied migration $migration" . PHP_EOL;


//Basiclly  we have to append the namespace to the classname so when we create object, the object knows from which namespace should be created.

